{"type":"message","id":"28f3a13c","parentId":"8bb6969f","timestamp":"2026-03-19T08:45:26.586Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The context monitor has run and detected that the main session is at 72% context usage (143,973 / 200,000 tokens), which exceeds the 60% threshold.\n\nAccording to the skill description for context-manager, it should automatically create a new session with loaded memory when 85% threshold is reached. But this is a warning at 72%.\n\nLet me check what the current context state is and whether we need to take action. The script mentions checking memory files - let me also check what's in the memory-lite file.\n\nActually, looking at the cron context, this is just a context monitor check. The context manager skill says it triggers at 85% threshold. We're at 72% now, so no automatic session switch is needed yet.\n\nI should report this status to the user as a heartbeat-style check.","thinkingSignature":"ed8429499fdc2bfdab714ac73c48501638fd667013f962e913f3f70ab0264913"},{"type":"text","text":"📊 **Context Monitor Report**\n\n| Metric | Value |\n|--------|-------|\n| Context Usage | **72%** (143,973 / 200,000 tokens) |\n| Threshold | 60% |\n| Status | ⚠️ Above threshold |\n\nCurrent usage is at 72%, which exceeds the 60% warning threshold but below the 85% auto-switch threshold. Everything is still functioning normally, but you may want to consider starting a new session soon to avoid interruption.\n\nHEARTBEAT_OK"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":1279,"output":275,"cacheRead":37002,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":38556,"cost":{"input":0.0003837,"output":0.00033,"cacheRead":0.00111006,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.00182376}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773909914539}}
